    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Section B: Gradient Boosting\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Referencing the getting started docs...\\n\",\n",
    "    \"https://scikit-learn.org/stable/getting_started.html\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Turns out, I needed to add passthrough preprocessor that does nothing.\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"id\": \"8fb5106499fe212c\"\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Section C: Random Forest\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Learning what are random forests and how to implement:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"A random forest algorithm is basically...\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. generate multiple random decision trees\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. figure out the output for each tree\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. majority vote\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"I first need to implement generating decision trees. Referencing the resources from Professor Stern:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"* https://quantdare.com/decision-trees-gini-vs-entropy/\\n\",\n",
    "    \"* https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/machine-learning/random-forest-algorithm-in-machine-learning/\\n\",\n",
    "    \"* https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/machine-learning/decision-tree/\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"So decision trees are consisted of...\\n\",\n",
    "    \"* parent nodes: dataset\\n\",\n",
    "    \"* internal nodes: contains boolean(classification) or inequality statement(regression)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"* edges: parameters iaw parent nodes' condition\\n\",\n",
    "    \"* leaf nodes: contains samples meeting the conditions of the internal nodes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"What do I then need to implement this data structure?\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"id\": \"976b2c74545a184d\"\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {\n",
    "    \"ExecuteTime\": {\n",
    "     \"end_time\": \"2025-12-08T03:46:01.650786Z\",\n",
    "     \"start_time\": \"2025-12-08T03:46:01.640654Z\"\n",
    "    }\n",
    "   },\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"df = sp.preprocess_data(sp.load_data())\\n\",\n",
    "    \"X = df.drop(columns=[\\\"at_risk\\\"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"y = df[\\\"at_risk\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"\\\\nGETTING GINI VALUE FOR BOOLEAN VALUES\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"true_count = len(X[X[\\\"failures\\\"] == 1])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"false_count = len(X[X[\\\"failures\\\"] == 0])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"total = true_count + false_count\\n\",\n",
    "    \"true_prob = true_count / total\\n\",\n",
    "    \"false_prob = false_count / total\\n\",\n",
    "    \"gini = 1 - (true_prob**2 + false_prob**2)\\n\",\n",
